      <section eId="sec_55_0109">
        <num>55-0109</num>
        <heading>Special groundwater protection areas; nomination</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_55_0109__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>whether the special groundwater protection area is a recharge zone\nfor groundwater with a present or future water supply potential;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_55_0109__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>whether the special groundwater protection area is largely\nundeveloped with tracts of natural vegetation, or natural geological\nconditions;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_55_0109__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>whether the groundwater which is recharged through the special\ngroundwater protection area is of high quality;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_55_0109__subsec_d">
          <num>(d)</num>
          <content>
            <p>whether the hydrogeologic conditions are such that development\ncould lead to degradation of water quality;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_55_0109__subsec_e">
          <num>(e)</num>
          <content>
            <p>whether portions of the groundwater within the sole source aquifer\narea are already contaminated with toxic organics, nutrients, salts or\nother pollutants so as to warrant special protection for areas which\nrecharge high quality groundwater;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_55_0109__subsec_f">
          <num>(f)</num>
          <content>
            <p>whether maintenance of existing high quality in the groundwater\nrecharged through the special groundwater protection area would have\nsignificant economic, social, ecological, recreational or aesthetic\nbenefits for the sole source aquifer area; and\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_55_0109__subsec_g">
          <num>(g)</num>
          <content>
            <p>whether degradation of such groundwater would have significant\neconomic, social, ecological, recreational and aesthetic costs for the\narea.\n  3. The nomination petition shall also identify:\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_55_0109__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>the preliminary boundaries of the special groundwater protection\narea or areas;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_55_0109__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>a brief outline of the plan of work;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_55_0109__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>a tentative membership list for any advisory committees; and\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_55_0109__subsec_d">
          <num>(d)</num>
          <content>
            <p>a reasonable budget request for the project.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
